$ "Decompose" x^n - 1 "with" n in [5, 12] "in" ZZ[x] $
$x^(p - 1) + ... + 1$ is prime 

$x^5 - 1 = (x - 1)(x^4 + ... + 1)$

$x^6 - 1 = (x^3 - 1)(x^3 + 1) = (x - 1)(x^2 + x + 1)(x^2 - x + 1)(x + 1)$

$x^7 - 1 = (x - 1)(x^6 + ... + 1)$

$x^8 - 1 = (x - 1)(x + 1)(x^2 + 1)(x^4 + 1) = (x - 1)(x + 1)(x^2 + 1)(x^4 + 1)$

$x^9 - 1 = (x^3 - 1)(x^6 + x^3 + 1) = (x - 1)(x^2 + x + 1)(x^6 + x^3 + 1)$

$x^10 - 1 =
(x^5 - 1)(x^5 + 1) =
(x - 1)(x^4 + ... + 1)(x + 1)(x^4 - x^3 + x^2 - x + 1)$

$x^11 - 1 = (x - 1)(x^10 + ... + 1)$

$x^12 - 1 = (x^6 - 1)(x^6 + 1)$

